On 9/9/11 7:36 AM, Tom Tarka wrote:
> Friday topic: When you sleep on the lower bed of your camper, do your feet
> face the front or rear of the bus?


I keep my feet above my head.  When everything is level I sleep with my 
feet to the rear.  This avoids encounters with the headbanger cabinet.  
That may not work for a taller person.  As for the support of the end of 
the bed the westy brackets should be sufficient to hold ample sized 
people :)
